turn.2: PF (firewall)  PF (Packet Filter, also written pf) is a BSD licensed stateful packet filter, a central piece of software for firewalling.
turn.4: It is comparable to netfilter (iptables), ipfw, and ipfilter.
turn.5: What are some other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.6: PF was developed for OpenBSD, but has been ported to many other operating systems.
turn.8: PF was originally designed as replacement for Darren Reed's IPFilter, from which it derives much of its rule syntax.
turn.10: IPFilter was removed from OpenBSD's CVS tree on 30 May 2001 due to OpenBSD developers' concerns with its license.
turn.12: The initial version of PF was written by Daniel Hartmeier.
